#: ../../S/smoke-and-mirrors.rst:5
msgid "smoke and mirrors"
msgstr "smoke and mirrors"

#: ../../S/smoke-and-mirrors.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../S/smoke-and-mirrors.rst:9
msgid ""
"Marketing deceptions. The term is mainstream in this general sense. Among "
"hackers it's strongly associated with bogus demos and crocked "
":ref:`benchmark`\\s (see also :ref:`MIPS`\\, :ref:`machoflops`\\). \"They "
"claim their new box cranks 50 MIPS for under $5000, but didn't specify the "
"instruction mix — sounds like smoke and mirrors to me.\" The phrase, "
"popularized by newspaper columnist Jimmy Breslin c.1975, has been said to "
"derive from carnie slang for magic acts and ‘freak show’ displays that "
"depend on *trompe l'oeil* effects, but also calls to mind the fierce Aztec "
"god Tezcatlipoca (lit. \"Smoking Mirror\") for whom the hearts of huge "
"numbers of human sacrificial victims were regularly cut out. Upon hearing "
"about a rigged demo or yet another round of fantasy-based marketing "
"promises, hackers often feel analogously disheartened. See also "
":ref:`stealth-manager`\\."
msgstr ""
"マーケティングの欺瞞。この用語は、この一般的な意味では主流である。ハッカーの間では、いんちきなデモやごまかした\\ :ref:`benchmark`\\"
" と強く結びついている(\\ :ref:`MIPS`\\ 、\\ :ref:`machoflops`\\ "
"も参照)。「彼らは新しい箱が5000ドル未満で50 MIPSを叩き出すと主張しているが、命令ミックスを明示しなかった——私にはsmoke and "
"mirrorsに聞こえる。」このフレーズは、新聞コラムニストのJimmy "
"Breslinが1975年頃に広めたもので、マジックの演技や、だまし絵効果に依存する‘見世物小屋’の出し物を指すカーニバルの俗語に由来するとされてきたが、無数の人間の生贄の心臓が定期的にえぐり出された、荒々しいアステカの神Tezcatlipoca(文字どおり「煙を吐く鏡」)をも想起させる。やらせのデモや、また一巡りの空想に基づくマーケティングの約束について聞かされると、ハッカーはしばしば同じように気落ちする。\\"
" :ref:`stealth-manager`\\ も参照。"
